---
import Page from '../../../layouts/Page.astro';
import FAQ from '../../../components/FAQ.astro';

const title = 'Cat Age Calculator — Convert Cat Years to Human Years';
const description = 'Convert your cat\'s age to human years using the AVMA/AAFP-aligned 15-24-4 model. Find your cat\'s life stage and vet-backed health milestones.';
const image = '/images/hero.jpg';

const breadcrumbs = [
	{ label: 'Home', href: '/' },
	{ label: 'Tools', href: '/tools/' },
	{ label: 'Cat Age Calculator', href: '/tools/cat-age-calculator/' },
];

const faqItems = [
	{
		question: 'Is the "one cat year equals seven human years" rule accurate?',
		answer: 'No. Cats mature rapidly in their first two years. The first year is roughly equivalent to 15 human years, the second year adds about 9 more, and each year after that adds roughly 4 human years.'
	},
	{
		question: 'What is the scientific basis for this calculator?',
		answer: 'This calculator uses the three-stage model widely cited by the AVMA and pet-health organizations: year 1 ≈ 15 human years, year 2 ≈ +9, and each year after ≈ +4. Life-stage labels follow the 2021 AAHA/AAFP Feline Life Stage Guidelines.'
	},
	{
		question: 'When is a cat considered a senior?',
		answer: 'The 2021 AAHA/AAFP Feline Life Stage Guidelines define cats over 10 years old as senior. Cats aged 15 and older are sometimes called geriatric or super-senior.'
	},
	{
		question: 'Can this calculator replace a veterinary exam?',
		answer: 'No. This tool provides an estimate for educational purposes only. Always consult a licensed veterinarian for health assessments, especially for senior or geriatric cats.'
	},
	{
		question: 'Do indoor and outdoor cats age differently?',
		answer: 'This calculator does not distinguish between indoor and outdoor cats. Outdoor cats often face more environmental risks, but the basic aging model is similar. Individual health, genetics, and care have a much larger impact than lifestyle alone.'
	}
];

const schemaJson = {
	'@context': 'https://schema.org',
	'@type': 'SoftwareApplication',
	name: 'Cat Age Calculator',
	applicationCategory: 'HealthApplication',
	operatingSystem: 'Any',
	offers: {
		'@type': 'Offer',
		price: '0',
		priceCurrency: 'USD'
	},
	publisher: {
		'@type': 'Organization',
		name: 'The Caring Pet'
	},
	description: description
};
---

<Page title={title} description={description} image={image} breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}>
	<script type="application/ld+json" is:inline set:html={JSON.stringify(schemaJson)} slot="head" />

	<section class="calculator-section">
		<div class="card calculator-card">
			<h2 class="calculator-title">Calculate Your Cat's Human Age</h2>
			<p class="text-muted calculator-intro">Enter your cat's age. The result is an estimate based on veterinary age-guidelines.</p>

			<form id="cat-age-form" class="calculator-form" novalidate>
				<div class="form-row">
					<div class="form-group years-group">
						<label for="cat-years">Years</label>
						<div class="stepper">
							<button type="button" class="stepper-btn" data-stepper="down" aria-label="Decrease years">−</button>
							<input type="number" id="cat-years" name="years" min="0" max="30" value="0" aria-label="Years" />
							<button type="button" class="stepper-btn" data-stepper="up" aria-label="Increase years">+</button>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="form-group months-group">
						<label>Months</label>
						<div class="month-pills" role="radiogroup" aria-label="Months">
							{Array.from({ length: 12 }, (_, i) => (
								<label class="month-pill">
									<input type="radio" name="months" value={i} checked={i === 0} />
									<span>{i}</span>
								</label>
							))}
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg calculate-btn">Calculate</button>
			</form>

			<div id="cat-result-panel" class="result-panel" hidden aria-live="polite">
				<div class="result-main">
					<span class="result-label">Your cat is about</span>
					<div class="result-age">
						<span data-human-age>—</span>
						<span class="result-unit">human years old</span>
					</div>
					<span data-life-stage-badge class="badge badge-secondary life-stage-badge">—</span>
					<p data-life-stage-desc class="result-stage-desc">—</p>
				</div>
				<div class="result-actions">
					<button id="cat-share-btn" class="btn btn-secondary" type="button">Share result</button>
					<span id="cat-share-feedback" class="share-feedback" hidden role="status" aria-live="polite"></span>
				</div>
			</div>

			<p id="cat-error-message" class="error-message" hidden>
				<svg class="error-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
					<circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
					<line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/>
					<line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"/>
				</svg>
				<span class="error-text">Please enter a valid age greater than 0.</span>
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section-content">
		<h2>How This Calculator Works</h2>
		<p>
			The idea that one cat year equals seven human years is a rough oversimplification. Cats age quickly in their first two years — reaching the equivalent of a young adult human by age two — and then their aging rate slows.
		</p>
		<p>
			This calculator uses the veterinary-aligned three-stage model:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Year 1</strong> ≈ 15 human years</li>
			<li><strong>Year 2</strong> ≈ +9 human years (total ≈ 24)</li>
			<li><strong>Each year after</strong> ≈ +4 human years</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			This model is widely used in client education by the <a href="https://www.avma.org/resources-tools/reports/avma-animal-health-studies-database" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">American Veterinary Medical Association (AVMA)</a>, aligns with the <a href="https://www.aaha.org/resources/2021-aaha-aafp-feline-life-stage-guidelines/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">2021 AAHA/AAFP Feline Life Stage Guidelines</a>, and is published by <a href="https://icatcare.org/articles/how-to-tell-your-cats-age-in-human-years" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">International Cat Care</a>.
		</p>
		<p class="text-small text-muted">
			<strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This calculator provides estimates for educational purposes only and is not a substitute for professional veterinary advice, diagnosis, or treatment.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="section-content">
		<h2>Cat Age Comparison Chart</h2>
		<p class="text-muted">Human-age equivalents by cat age. These are estimates, not exact conversions.</p>
		<div class="table-wrapper">
			<table>
				<thead>
					<tr>
						<th>Cat Years</th>
						<th>Human Years</th>
						<th>Life Stage</th>
					</tr>
				</thead>
				<tbody>
					<tr><td>3 months</td><td>4</td><td>Kitten</td></tr>
					<tr><td>6 months</td><td>8</td><td>Kitten</td></tr>
					<tr><td>1 year</td><td>15</td><td>Young Adult</td></tr>
					<tr><td>2 years</td><td>24</td><td>Young Adult</td></tr>
					<tr><td>3 years</td><td>28</td><td>Young Adult</td></tr>
					<tr><td>5 years</td><td>36</td><td>Young Adult</td></tr>
					<tr><td>7 years</td><td>44</td><td>Mature Adult</td></tr>
					<tr><td>10 years</td><td>56</td><td>Senior</td></tr>
					<tr><td>12 years</td><td>64</td><td>Senior</td></tr>
					<tr><td>15 years</td><td>76</td><td>Geriatric</td></tr>
					<tr><td>18 years</td><td>88</td><td>Geriatric</td></tr>
					<tr><td>20 years</td><td>96</td><td>Geriatric</td></tr>
				</tbody>
			</table>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section-content">
		<h2>Health Milestones by Life Stage</h2>
		<p class="text-muted">Use these general milestones as a conversation starter with your veterinarian.</p>

		<div class="milestone-grid">
			<div class="milestone-card">
				<span class="milestone-icon">🐱</span>
				<h3>Kitten</h3>
				<p><strong>0–1 year</strong></p>
				<ul>
					<li>Core vaccination series</li>
					<li>Spay/neuter planning</li>
					<li>Socialization and litter training</li>
					<li>Introduce safe feeding routines</li>
				</ul>
				<p><a href="/blog/why-does-my-dog-eat-so-fast/">Why does my pet eat so fast?</a> · <a href="/blog/slow-feeder-bowl-size-guide/">Slow feeder bowl size guide</a></p>
			</div>

			<div class="milestone-card">
				<span class="milestone-icon">🎾</span>
				<h3>Young Adult</h3>
				<p><strong>1–6 years</strong></p>
				<ul>
					<li>Annual wellness exam</li>
					<li>Dental assessment and home care</li>
					<li>Weight and body-condition monitoring</li>
					<li>Establish play and enrichment routines</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="milestone-card">
				<span class="milestone-icon">💪</span>
				<h3>Mature Adult</h3>
				<p><strong>7–10 years</strong></p>
				<ul>
					<li>Continue annual exams</li>
					<li>Screen for early kidney and thyroid changes</li>
					<li>Maintain dental health</li>
					<li>Adjust calories to prevent weight gain</li>
				</ul>
				<p><a href="/blog/best-slow-feeder-dog-bowls/">Best slow feeder bowls</a> · <a href="/blog/best-puzzle-feeders-for-anxious-dogs/">Best puzzle feeders</a></p>
			</div>

			<div class="milestone-card">
				<span class="milestone-icon">🩺</span>
				<h3>Senior</h3>
				<p><strong>11–14 years</strong></p>
				<ul>
					<li>Semi-annual vet visits</li>
					<li>Bloodwork, urinalysis, blood pressure</li>
					<li>Joint comfort and mobility support</li>
					<li>Easy-access food and water stations</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="milestone-card">
				<span class="milestone-icon">🏠</span>
				<h3>Geriatric</h3>
				<p><strong>15+ years</strong></p>
				<ul>
					<li>Pain, mobility, and cognitive assessments</li>
					<li>More frequent veterinary check-ins</li>
					<li>Home comfort modifications</li>
					<li>Quality-of-life planning with your vet</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section-content">
		<h2>Related Feeding Guides</h2>
		<ul class="related-list">
			<li><a href="/blog/best-slow-feeder-dog-bowls/">Best Slow Feeder Dog Bowls</a> — Help fast eaters slow down safely.</li>
			<li><a href="/blog/why-does-my-dog-eat-so-fast/">Why Does My Dog Eat So Fast?</a> — Causes, risks, and vet-backed solutions.</li>
			<li><a href="/blog/slow-feeder-bowl-size-guide/">Slow Feeder Bowl Size Guide</a> — Choose the right bowl for your pet's build.</li>
			<li><a href="/blog/best-puzzle-feeders-for-anxious-dogs/">Best Puzzle Feeders for Anxious Dogs</a> — Mental enrichment for mealtime.</li>
			<li><a href="/blog/best-lick-mats-for-dogs/">Best Lick Mats for Dogs</a> — Calming enrichment for all life stages.</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="section-content">
		<h2>Other Pet Age Calculators</h2>
		<p>
			Have a dog? Try our <a href="/tools/dog-age-calculator/">Dog Age Calculator</a> for a size-based estimate.
		</p>
	</section>

	<FAQ items={faqItems} />
	<script is:inline>
	const LIFE_STAGES = {
		kitten: {
			label: 'Kitten',
			description: 'Rapid growth, vaccinations, and socialization.'
		},
		youngAdult: {
			label: 'Young Adult',
			description: 'Physically mature; focus on prevention and healthy routines.'
		},
		matureAdult: {
			label: 'Mature Adult',
			description: 'Stable prime years; watch weight and early disease signs.'
		},
		senior: {
			label: 'Senior',
			description: 'Slowing metabolism; increase screening and comfort support.'
		},
		geriatric: {
			label: 'Geriatric',
			description: 'Advanced age; prioritize comfort, mobility, and quality of life.'
		}
	};

	function calculateHumanAge(years, months) {
		const ageYears = years + months / 12;
		if (ageYears <= 1) {
			return Math.round(ageYears * 15);
		}
		if (ageYears <= 2) {
			return Math.round(15 + (ageYears - 1) * 9);
		}
		return Math.round(24 + (ageYears - 2) * 4);
	}

	function getLifeStage(ageYears) {
		if (ageYears < 1) return 'kitten';
		if (ageYears <= 6) return 'youngAdult';
		if (ageYears <= 10) return 'matureAdult';
		if (ageYears <= 14) return 'senior';
		return 'geriatric';
	}

	function formatAgeText(years, months) {
		if (years === 0) return `${months}-month-old`;
		if (months === 0) return `${years}-year-old`;
		return `${years}-year, ${months}-month-old`;
	}

	const form = document.getElementById('cat-age-form');
	const yearsInput = document.getElementById('cat-years');
	const resultPanel = document.getElementById('cat-result-panel');
	const errorMessage = document.getElementById('cat-error-message');
	const shareBtn = document.getElementById('cat-share-btn');
	const shareFeedback = document.getElementById('cat-share-feedback');

	let lastResult = null;

	function getYearsValue() {
		return parseInt(yearsInput.value, 10) || 0;
	}

	function getMonthsValue() {
		const checked = form.querySelector('input[name="months"]:checked');
		return checked ? parseInt(checked.value, 10) : 0;
	}

	function showError(message) {
		errorMessage.querySelector('.error-text').textContent = message;
		errorMessage.hidden = false;
		resultPanel.hidden = true;
	}

	function hideError() {
		errorMessage.hidden = true;
	}

	function validate(years, months) {
		if (Number.isNaN(years) || years < 0) {
			return 'Please enter a valid number of years.';
		}
		if (years > 30) {
			return 'Please enter an age of 30 years or less.';
		}
		if (Number.isNaN(months) || months < 0 || months > 11) {
			return 'Please select a valid month value (0–11).';
		}
		if (years === 0 && months === 0) {
			return 'Please enter an age greater than 0.';
		}
		return null;
	}

	function updateYears(change) {
		const current = getYearsValue();
		const min = parseInt(yearsInput.min, 10);
		const max = parseInt(yearsInput.max, 10);
		const next = Math.min(Math.max(current + change, min), max);
		yearsInput.value = next;
		hideError();
	}

	form?.querySelectorAll('[data-stepper]').forEach((btn) => {
		btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
			const change = btn.dataset.stepper === 'up' ? 1 : -1;
			updateYears(change);
		});
	});

	yearsInput?.addEventListener('input', () => {
		hideError();
	});

	yearsInput?.addEventListener('blur', () => {
		const value = getYearsValue();
		const min = parseInt(yearsInput.min, 10);
		const max = parseInt(yearsInput.max, 10);
		if (value < min) yearsInput.value = min;
		if (value > max) yearsInput.value = max;
	});

	form?.querySelectorAll('input[name="months"]').forEach((radio) => {
		radio.addEventListener('change', hideError);
	});

	form?.addEventListener('submit', (e) => {
		e.preventDefault();

		const years = getYearsValue();
		const months = getMonthsValue();

		const error = validate(years, months);
		if (error) {
			showError(error);
			return;
		}

		hideError();

		const ageYears = years + months / 12;
		const humanAge = calculateHumanAge(years, months);
		const stageKey = getLifeStage(ageYears);
		const stage = LIFE_STAGES[stageKey];

		resultPanel.querySelector('[data-human-age]').textContent = humanAge;
		resultPanel.querySelector('[data-life-stage-badge]').textContent = stage.label;
		resultPanel.querySelector('[data-life-stage-desc]').textContent = stage.description;

		lastResult = {
			years,
			months,
			humanAge,
			stageLabel: stage.label
		};

		resultPanel.hidden = false;
		resultPanel.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'nearest' });
	});

	function buildShareText(result) {
		return `🐱 Wait, my cat is basically ${result.humanAge} years old?!\nAccording to the cat age calculator, ${result.years} years and ${result.months} months puts them in the ${result.stageLabel} stage.\nSee how old your cat really is → https://thecaringpet.com/tools/cat-age-calculator/`;
	}

	function buildShareData(shareText) {
		return {
			title: 'Cat Age Calculator — The Caring Pet',
			text: shareText,
			url: 'https://thecaringpet.com/tools/cat-age-calculator/'
		};
	}

	async function copyToClipboard(text) {
		if (navigator.clipboard && window.isSecureContext) {
			try {
				await navigator.clipboard.writeText(text);
				return true;
			} catch (err) {
				console.error('Clipboard API failed:', err);
			}
		}
		return copyWithExecCommand(text);
	}

	function copyWithExecCommand(text) {
		const textarea = document.createElement('textarea');
		textarea.value = text;
		textarea.setAttribute('readonly', '');
		textarea.style.cssText = 'position:fixed;left:-9999px;top:-9999px;opacity:0;';
		document.body.appendChild(textarea);
		textarea.focus();
		textarea.select();
		textarea.setSelectionRange(0, text.length);

		let success = false;
		try {
			success = document.execCommand('copy');
		} catch (err) {
			console.error('execCommand copy failed:', err);
		}

		if (textarea.parentNode) {
			document.body.removeChild(textarea);
		}
		return success;
	}

	function showShareFeedback(message, type) {
		if (!shareFeedback) return;
		shareFeedback.textContent = message;
		shareFeedback.className = `share-feedback share-feedback--${type}`;
		shareFeedback.hidden = false;
		clearTimeout(shareFeedback._hideTimeout);
		shareFeedback._hideTimeout = setTimeout(() => {
			shareFeedback.hidden = true;
		}, 2500);
	}

	shareBtn?.addEventListener('click', async () => {
		if (!lastResult) return;

		const shareText = buildShareText(lastResult);
		const shareData = buildShareData(shareText);

		try {
			if (typeof navigator.share === 'function') {
				await navigator.share(shareData);
				return;
			}
		} catch (err) {
			if (err.name === 'AbortError') return;
			console.error('Native share failed, falling back to clipboard:', err);
		}

		const copied = await copyToClipboard(shareText);
		if (copied) {
			showShareFeedback('Copied to clipboard!', 'success');
		} else {
			showShareFeedback('Unable to copy. Please copy the text manually.', 'error');
		}
	});
	</script>
</Page>

<style>
	.calculator-section {
		margin-bottom: var(--spacing-2xl);
	}

	.calculator-card {
		padding: var(--spacing-xl);
	}

	.calculator-title {
		margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
		font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 2rem);
	}

	.calculator-intro {
		margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
	}

	.calculator-form {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: var(--spacing-lg);
	}

	.form-row {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		gap: var(--spacing-md);
	}

	@media (min-width: 480px) {
		.form-row {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr;
		}
	}

	.form-group {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: var(--spacing-xs);
	}

	.form-group label {
		font-weight: 600;
		font-size: 0.95rem;
	}

	/* Years stepper */
	.stepper {
		display: flex;
		align-items: stretch;
		border: 1px solid hsl(var(--border));
		border-radius: var(--radius-md);
		overflow: hidden;
		background-color: hsl(var(--card));
	}

	.stepper input[type="number"] {
		flex: 1;
		border: none;
		border-radius: 0;
		text-align: center;
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 0.75rem 0.5rem;
		-moz-appearance: textfield;
	}

	.stepper input[type="number"]::-webkit-outer-spin-button,
	.stepper input[type="number"]::-webkit-inner-spin-button {
		-webkit-appearance: none;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.stepper-btn {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		width: 48px;
		border: none;
		background-color: hsl(var(--muted));
		color: hsl(var(--foreground));
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		cursor: pointer;
		transition: background-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.stepper-btn:hover {
		background-color: hsl(var(--primary) / 0.12);
	}

	.stepper-btn:active {
		background-color: hsl(var(--primary) / 0.2);
	}

	/* Months pills */
	.month-pills {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(6, 1fr);
		gap: var(--spacing-xs);
	}

	.month-pill {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		aspect-ratio: 1;
		border: 1px solid hsl(var(--border));
		border-radius: var(--radius-md);
		cursor: pointer;
		background-color: hsl(var(--card));
		transition: all 0.2s ease;
		position: relative;
	}

	.month-pill:hover {
		border-color: hsl(var(--primary));
		background-color: hsl(var(--primary) / 0.03);
	}

	.month-pill input[type="radio"] {
		position: absolute;
		opacity: 0;
		width: 0;
		height: 0;
	}

	.month-pill span {
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: hsl(var(--foreground));
	}

	.month-pill:has(input:checked) {
		border-color: hsl(var(--primary));
		background-color: hsl(var(--primary));
		box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px hsl(var(--primary));
	}

	.month-pill:has(input:checked) span {
		color: hsl(var(--primary-foreground));
	}

	.calculate-btn {
		width: 100%;
	}

	.result-panel {
		margin-top: var(--spacing-xl);
		padding: var(--spacing-xl);
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, hsl(var(--primary) / 0.08) 0%, hsl(var(--secondary) / 0.06) 100%);
		border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
		border: 1px solid hsl(var(--primary) / 0.15);
		text-align: center;
	}

	.result-label {
		display: block;
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		color: hsl(var(--muted-foreground));
		margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
	}

	.result-age {
		display: flex;
		align-items: baseline;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: var(--spacing-sm);
		margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
